{
  "info": {
    "name": "Oraclous \u2014 Fresh User",
    "description": "End-to-end flow for a fresh user: register \u2192 bootstrap workspace \u2192 run an assessment. Tokens and IDs auto-save between requests via test scripts. Set the two `*_base_url` variables once for your environment (defaults are local docker compose) and the rest fills itself in.\n\n**Order of operations** (top to bottom):\n1. Auth \u2192 Register OR Login (auto-saves `access_token` and `refresh_token`)\n2. Onboarding \u2192 Bootstrap (auto-saves new `access_token` carrying `home_graph_id`, plus `graph_id`)\n3. Assessments \u2192 Create Run (auto-saves `run_id`)\n4. Anything else.\n\nIf you signed in via Google OAuth on the frontend, paste your existing `access_token` into the collection variable and skip the Register/Login step \u2014 Bootstrap works the same either way.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "auth_base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8000",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "kgb_base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:8003",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "email",
      "value": "r.jahankohan@gmail.com",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "password",
      "value": "changeme",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "access_token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "refresh_token",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "graph_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "run_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{access_token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "01 \u2014 Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register (email + password)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{auth_base_url}}/register/",
              "host": [
                "{{auth_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "register",
                ""
              ]
            },
            "description": "Creates a new user and returns access + refresh tokens. The returned access_token has NO workspace pointer yet \u2014 call Onboarding \u2192 Bootstrap next.\n\nRate limited to 5/minute. Returns 409 if the email is already registered (just call Login instead)."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201 || pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', json.refresh_token);",
                  "  console.log('Saved access_token + refresh_token. NOTE: this token does NOT yet carry home_graph_id \u2014 call Bootstrap next.');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login (email + password)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{auth_base_url}}/login/",
              "host": [
                "{{auth_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "login",
                ""
              ]
            },
            "description": "Logs in an existing user. The returned access_token will carry home_graph_id IF you've already been through Bootstrap before. If not, call Bootstrap after this.\n\nRate limited to 10/minute."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', json.refresh_token);",
                  "  console.log('Saved access_token + refresh_token.');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh access token",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"refresh_token\": \"{{refresh_token}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{auth_base_url}}/refresh/",
              "host": [
                "{{auth_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "refresh",
                ""
              ]
            },
            "description": "Exchange your refresh_token for a fresh access_token. Use this when the access_token has expired (24h default) but the refresh_token is still valid (7 days default)."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', json.refresh_token);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Who am I (/me)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{auth_base_url}}/me",
              "host": [
                "{{auth_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "me"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns the current user's profile, including `home_graph_id` if Bootstrap has run. Use this to check whether you still need to Bootstrap or not."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "02 \u2014 Onboarding",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Bootstrap workspace (one-call setup)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"workspace_name\": \"Reza Workspace\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kgb_base_url}}/api/v1/onboarding/bootstrap",
              "host": [
                "{{kgb_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "onboarding",
                "bootstrap"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Three things in one call:\n1. Creates a default workspace (graph) for you.\n2. Binds it as your default \u2014 your user record now points at it.\n3. Mints a FRESH access_token + refresh_token that name the workspace.\n\n**Idempotent.** If you call it twice, the second call returns the existing workspace and `already_initialized: true`. No second workspace gets created.\n\n**Replaces your current tokens.** The test script overwrites `access_token` and `refresh_token` collection variables. Throw away the old ones \u2014 they don't name the workspace and the assessment endpoints will reject them."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', json.refresh_token);",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('graph_id', json.graph_id);",
                  "  console.log('Bootstrap complete.');",
                  "  console.log('  graph_id:           ' + json.graph_id);",
                  "  console.log('  workspace_name:     ' + json.workspace_name);",
                  "  console.log('  already_initialized:' + json.already_initialized);",
                  "  console.log('  NEW access_token saved (carries home_graph_id).');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "03 \u2014 Workspace",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kgb_base_url}}/api/v1/health",
              "host": [
                "{{kgb_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "health"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Sanity check: KGB + Neo4j + Postgres + Redis all healthy. No auth required."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List my workspaces",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kgb_base_url}}/api/v1/graphs",
              "host": [
                "{{kgb_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "graphs"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns all graphs the current user has access to via ReBAC. After Bootstrap, you'll see the one workspace it created."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "04 \u2014 Assessments \u2014 Writes",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create assessment run",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"template_slug\": \"assess-v1\",\n  \"subject\": {\n    \"slug\": \"eurail\",\n    \"name\": \"Eurail B.V.\",\n    \"vertical_slug\": \"rail-cooperative\",\n    \"domains\": [\"eurail.com\"],\n    \"aliases\": [\"Eurail\"]\n  },\n  \"cli_flags\": {\n    \"vertical\": \"rail-cooperative\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kgb_base_url}}/api/v1/assessments/runs",
              "host": [
                "{{kgb_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "assessments",
                "runs"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Bootstraps a new assessment run and its 23 ModuleRun rows in `planned` state. This is what /assess calls under the hood when you type the slash command in Claude Code.\n\n`graph_id` is taken from your access_token's `home_graph_id` claim \u2014 you do not (and cannot) pass it in the body."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201 || pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('run_id', json.run_id);",
                  "  console.log('Saved run_id: ' + json.run_id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Finalize run",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"status\": \"finished\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kgb_base_url}}/api/v1/assessments/runs/{{run_id}}:finalize",
              "host": [
                "{{kgb_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "assessments",
                "runs",
                "{{run_id}}:finalize"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Closes the run. Server-side citation-coverage gate decides whether status flips to `finished` or `failed`."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "05 \u2014 Assessments \u2014 Reads",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List runs (paginated)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kgb_base_url}}/api/v1/assessments/runs?limit=20",
              "host": [
                "{{kgb_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "assessments",
                "runs"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "limit",
                  "value": "20"
                },
                {
                  "key": "cursor",
                  "value": "",
                  "disabled": true
                },
                {
                  "key": "subject_slug",
                  "value": "eurail",
                  "disabled": true
                },
                {
                  "key": "status",
                  "value": "running",
                  "disabled": true
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Paginated list of all your runs. Pass `cursor` from the previous response to page forward."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get run summary",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kgb_base_url}}/api/v1/assessments/runs/{{run_id}}",
              "host": [
                "{{kgb_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "assessments",
                "runs",
                "{{run_id}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Run overview: counts of findings / conflicts / questions / deliverables, plus wave-by-wave module-run status. Useful to poll while a run is mid-flight."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List module runs",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kgb_base_url}}/api/v1/assessments/runs/{{run_id}}/module-runs",
              "host": [
                "{{kgb_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "assessments",
                "runs",
                "{{run_id}}",
                "module-runs"
              ]
            },
            "description": "All 23 modules with their current status (`planned`, `running`, `finished`, `failed`) plus per-module evidence count."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Query findings (filterable)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kgb_base_url}}/api/v1/assessments/runs/{{run_id}}/findings?limit=50",
              "host": [
                "{{kgb_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "assessments",
                "runs",
                "{{run_id}}",
                "findings"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "limit",
                  "value": "50"
                },
                {
                  "key": "cursor",
                  "value": "",
                  "disabled": true
                },
                {
                  "key": "module_slug",
                  "value": "competitor-analysis",
                  "disabled": true
                },
                {
                  "key": "label",
                  "value": "DIRECT",
                  "disabled": true
                },
                {
                  "key": "min_confidence",
                  "value": "0.7",
                  "disabled": true
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "All findings recorded for the run, filterable by module, label (DIRECT/INDIRECT/INFERRED), confidence, etc."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List conflicts",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kgb_base_url}}/api/v1/assessments/runs/{{run_id}}/conflicts",
              "host": [
                "{{kgb_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "assessments",
                "runs",
                "{{run_id}}",
                "conflicts"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Findings that contradict each other, with synthesis notes."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List unresolved questions",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kgb_base_url}}/api/v1/assessments/runs/{{run_id}}/unresolved-questions",
              "host": [
                "{{kgb_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "assessments",
                "runs",
                "{{run_id}}",
                "unresolved-questions"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Open gaps surfaced by research subagents. Drives the Wave 2 gap-research fan-out."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List deliverables",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kgb_base_url}}/api/v1/assessments/runs/{{run_id}}/deliverables",
              "host": [
                "{{kgb_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "assessments",
                "runs",
                "{{run_id}}",
                "deliverables"
              ]
            },
            "description": "All persisted deliverables (module summaries + the 5 final docs). Use the `Get deliverable content` request to fetch the bytes."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get deliverable content",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kgb_base_url}}/api/v1/assessments/runs/{{run_id}}/deliverables/REPLACE_WITH_DELIVERABLE_ID/content",
              "host": [
                "{{kgb_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "assessments",
                "runs",
                "{{run_id}}",
                "deliverables",
                "REPLACE_WITH_DELIVERABLE_ID",
                "content"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Stream the actual bytes of a deliverable from the Blob CAS. Replace REPLACE_WITH_DELIVERABLE_ID with one returned by the List deliverables request."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "06 \u2014 Live tail (SSE)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Tail run events (SSE)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "text/event-stream"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{kgb_base_url}}/api/v1/assessments/runs/{{run_id}}/events",
              "host": [
                "{{kgb_base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "assessments",
                "runs",
                "{{run_id}}",
                "events"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Server-Sent Events stream of run progress: module status changes, finding-count increments, heartbeats. Postman shows the stream in the response panel \u2014 leave it open to watch live.\n\nIf nothing appears for >30s, that's expected \u2014 heartbeats are throttled to every 30s when there's no other activity."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
